24,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-03 01:19:44+00:00,8387179,uiri/toml,5271761,nateprewitt,,,205306476,283836250,"Sorry this took so long to get around to. I've got the patch working now so you can have a mix of inline and standard tables with original formatting preserved.

This implementation is, at least in my opinion, the cleaner of the two options. Having the `InlineTableDict` as essentially a sentinel object is a bit silly but the `__repr__` implementation is less desirable. We'd need to rebundle all the logic for printing (`_dump_inline_table` and `_dump_value`) inside the class which creates a fair amount of redundant code. We could call the functions directly from the class but it seems wrong to use external functions for something that fundamental to the object.

We can obviously tweak this if you feel strongly about overwriting `__repr__` but this is the minimal required change to get what we want. When you've got a moment please me know your thoughts, thanks!",{},,User,False
