270,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-23 02:45:16+00:00,4946406,mher/flower,359120,AndreLobato,,,142206033,220876671,"On this last update I have rationalised the calls for table.draw(), that's because, on the first implementation (calling table.draw for every new task event), at some point, the page would start to do excessive calls (GET) and jam the flower main process with too much calls, also is not a good approach since does little usage if the data sent by the WS pipe. To solve this problem I just added a time counter and set the a time threshold of 10s between each table.draw call. Also it will only try to call draw on task-received events, on all others events would just update the table row data if present, making a better usage of data flowing in the WS protocol.  ",{},,User,False
