394,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-01 14:43:09+00:00,10074815,berdario/pew,425099,ryanhiebert,,,114621469,160986866,"I'm not convinced it's worth having two packages. It's extra confusion. I get not wanting for workarounds to have to stick around, but I think with system libraries like this, it's somewhat unavoidable.

----------------

I'll let folks coming to look at this know how I finally installed the latest version of `pew`: I used `pipsi` (https://github.com/mitsuhiko/pipsi). It creates a separate virtualenv for each package that you install, and exposes the binaries. This is a great way to avoid system conflicts that can't be resolved by simply using `pip --user`.",{},,User,False
