447,IssueCommentEvent,2015-01-12 00:16:28+00:00,5021892,hgrecco/pint,278566,hgrecco,,,53657836,69519240,"I had some free time. The situation is different when you disable the cache:

### Develop
Python 2.7.9
```
10000 loops, best of 3: 181 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 290 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 299 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 231 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 335 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 451 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 247 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 268 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 548 usec per loop
```

Python 3.4
```
1000 loops, best of 3: 227 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 385 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 393 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 238 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 458 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 582 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 337 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 327 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 711 usec per loop
```

### 0.6
Python 2.7.9
```
10000 loops, best of 3: 167 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 239 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 232 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 198 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 284 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 377 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 218 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 235 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 416 usec per loop
```

Python 3.4
```
10000 loops, best of 3: 217 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 302 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 323 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 262 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 393 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 472 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 264 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 322 usec per loop
1000 loops, best of 3: 559 usec per loop
```

I  think this means that in `0.6` parsing is faster (as expected because we use a mutable container) but `develop` is faster because somehow caching got better. Still interesting and useful.",{},,User,False
