453,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-07 04:55:56+00:00,5021892,hgrecco/pint,278566,hgrecco,,,23149779,193099491,"`delta_` units are generated automatically for all offset units when they are defined. Your suggestions about what to define and what not to define looks good to me.

Regarding what to support, I would like to support all common operations .... and even uncommon ones if their implementation is not complicated. This will require to clearly specify which operations we support and how they are implemented internally. There are a few details. For example, right now the `lhs` quantity define the output units. So `1 meter + 1 cm` returns a quantity in `meter`, while `1 cm + 1 meter` is in `cm`. But octave and dB are *generic delta units* so some operations will be implemented different.
We also need to define what happens when a multiplication between units of different kinds are combined. 

I would say that we start writing the specs and part of the implementation (it can be even in pseudo code) until we have a clear design. ",{},,User,False
