746,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-21 02:47:23+00:00,10144140,Diaoul/enzyme,20629530,aulemahal,,,177550455,248496171,"Enzyme is a EBML parser, a format MP4 doesn't use. Instead, in most cases, the tag information is stored in a ID3 tag, like MP3 files. I don't think it would be useful to add a mp4 support to enzyme as there's already other Python libs covering that.

For non-tag metadata, I'd refer you to *ffmpeg* (from [this stackoverflow answer](http://stackoverflow.com/a/17595882)). For tags,  I'd recommend [*pytaglib*](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytaglib).",{},,User,False
