827,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-04 02:28:41+00:00,30492678,facetoe/zenpy,1366896,facetoe,,,230897935,306013513,"Instead of updating each ticket individually, try building a list of tickets and updating them in batches of 100 at a time (zenpy.tickets.update() accepts a list also). You can save some API calls by populating the user cache ahead of time. Increase the user cache size to > your total users then execute `[u for u in zenpy_client.users.incremental(start_time)]` to populate the cache before entering the while loop.  

I'd also move the sleep statement into the `while` loop's scope and out of the `for` loop. Process the views and tickets then sleep for a bit before hitting them again. You might also be able to ignore a bunch of tickets by checking `ticket.comment_count` or whether the tags already include ""first_reply"" or ""no_reply"".

If you still recieve exceptions after trying these things post the full stacktrace.",{},,User,False
