1134,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-11 22:47:45+00:00,16331291,davisking/dlib,6259399,davisking,,,105846997,139679851,"Yeah moving the version numbers into the CMakeLists.txt file does make sense.  Once this PR is finished I'll update the scripts and whatnot in docs to extract the version information from cmake rather than the current set of files.

A few more issues (only tested in cygwin so far):
- When I tried to build dlib I got this error: `CMake Error at CMakeLists.txt:434 (install): install Library TARGETS given no DESTINATION!`.  Changing the install call to this `install(TARGETS dlib-shared EXPORT dlib LIBRARY DESTINATION lib ARCHIVE DESTINATION lib)` seems to fix it.
- When I compiled the examples via the usual `cd build; cmake ..; make` it now builds dlib two times, once for the shared library and once for the archive.  
- The examples also print `dlib is built in Release mode: you can install it with 'make install'` which shouldn't be printed in client cmake files.  Maybe the right way to do this whole thing is to have a folder somewhere, say `dlib/install`, that has a special CMakeLists.txt file in it which includes `dlib/cmake` but adds whatever is necessary to do a `make install`.  This way existing users are not troubled with the `make install` features we are talking about adding.
- Just being compiled in release mode should not disable asserts.  For example, I often do debugging with release mode and asserts enabled because I'm debugging some big computation and it takes forever if I run the code without optimizations.  So in this case I'll go into ccmake and turn on the asserts while in release mode.  What is important here for the installer is just that the dlib/config.h file permanently configures the asserts one way or another.  Probably the right thing is to have cmake tell dlib/config.h to set the asserts on/off based on the setting of the DLIB_ENABLE_ASSERTS option (which is defaulted to off in release mode).

Finally, when trying to run make on the makefile generated for building just the dlib folder I get a bunch of linker errors at the end that look like this:

Linking CXX shared library cygdlib.dll
CMakeFiles/dlib-shared.dir/gui_widgets/fonts.o:fonts.cpp:(.text+0x1b08): undefined reference to `XwcTextExtents'
CMakeFiles/dlib-shared.dir/gui_widgets/fonts.o:fonts.cpp:(.text+0x1b08): relocation truncated to fit: R_X86_64_PC32 against undefined symbol `XwcTextExtents'
CMakeFiles/dlib-shared.dir/gui_widgets/fonts.o:fonts.cpp:(.text+0x1b43): undefined reference to `XFreeGC'
CMakeFiles/dlib-shared.dir/gui_widgets/fonts.o:fonts.cpp:(.text+0x1b43): relocation truncated to fit: R_X86_64_PC32 against undefined symbol `XFreeGC'


Yeah, the cmake package documentation is a little confusing.  I've never set one up before though so I'm not sure how to do it :)",{},,User,False
