1734,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-12 18:27:47+00:00,21843083,rlabbe/filterpy,5308143,rlabbe,,,281134135,372415275,"Sorry, it never occured to me that somebody would be using these functions.

It is just a concatenation of .dot. 

dot3(A,B,C) => dot(dot(A, B), C)

that is safer than A.dot(B).dot(C) in case any of A, B, or C are not of type array. the dot function can accept scalars, for example, so if A=3, the latter will raise an exception since int does not implement .dot member function.
",{},OWNER,User,False
