1903,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-26 17:09:07+00:00,11929631,craffel/mir_eval,1190540,bmcfee,,,156851992,221933721,"> I would have thought the clicking would have been worse the way you're doing it, but I'm not hearing it even at higher sampling rate, so I am ok with doing it your way.

The trick here is clipping the unvoiced frequency measurements to 0, and then interpolating; this ensures at least a ramp (for linear) or smoother transition (quadratic, cubic) whenever entering or leaving voiced regions.  It's a little sharper than @justinsalamon's version since I don't explicitly force a minimum width of the ramp, so you do see some spread in the spectrogram at the low frequencies in my version.  I'm fine with this as well.  PR incoming.",{},,User,False
