2170,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-10 23:49:11+00:00,9289343,svinota/pyroute2,216803,vodik,,,241863724,314281490,"Awesome, thanks!

Technically, all you really need to handle the import error on readline and continue without using it. Everything else should continue to work sans completer. The trick I personally like to do is something like:

```python
def _setup_readline(completer):
    import readline
    readline.set_history_length(100)
    readline.parse_and_bind('tab: complete')
    readline.set_completer(completer)
    readline.set_completer_delims(' \t\n.')
```

And just ignore import errors.",{},,User,False
