2342,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-26 03:59:16+00:00,5934517,dpkp/kafka-python,9140744,ayiis,,,150808430,214605990,"It worked.

It reminds me that there is a [new consumer](http://kafka.apache.org/documentation.html#newconsumerconfigs) in kafka-0.9.0 I'm using.

When I passing `api_version=auto` by default, `check_version()` set `api_version` to 0.9, so I should use

```bash
bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh --new-consumer --list
```

instead of

```bash
bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh --list
```

By the way,  passing `api_version='0.8.x'` to KafkaConsumer doesn't work in this case, but never mind.

Thanks to you.",{},,User,False
