2368,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-08 17:47:03+00:00,5934517,dpkp/kafka-python,843444,dpkp,,,280423472,350326672,"When you pass a topic name to the KafkaConsumer constructor, `KafkaConsumer('test', ...)`, you are using dynamic partition assignment and there is no guarantee that any partitions are assigned (if there are other consumers in the group) or when they will be assigned (depends on rebalance and network operations).

If you want strict control over partition assignment, try `consumer.assign([...])`",{},OWNER,User,False
