2370,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-13 16:30:59+00:00,5934517,dpkp/kafka-python,2366527,rmechler,,,279889575,351445080,"Thanks. It's when my colleague pointed out that my test server should do multiple small writes that things started to click. :)

So it seems like we have a degenerate case: SSL + lots of topics and partitions + relatively low traffic with periods of idle. We can address this to a fair degree on our end by (a) consolidating some of our topics and reducing the number of partitions in some cases, and (b) reducing the frequency of fetches in idle time using fetch_min_bytes and fetch_max_wait.

Nevertheless, it seems there is some efficiency to be gained in kafka-python by trying to read as many records as possible before doing another poll. Are you open to that idea?",{},NONE,User,False
