2668,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-03 12:53:10+00:00,5598737,BurntSushi/nflgame,2996205,ochawkeye,,,114790264,153342294,"How are you retrieving player stats for a single game?

Here is one way to get for a single week:
```python
import nflgame
games = nflgame.games(year=2015, week=8)
players = nflgame.combine_game_stats(games)
for player in players:
    print player, player.formatted_stats()
```

To do that for an entire season, just omit the week.
```python
import nflgame
games = nflgame.games(year=2015)
players = nflgame.combine_game_stats(games)
for player in players:
    print player, player.formatted_stats()
```

Worth noting, week can also be a list of weeks:
```python
import nflgame
games = nflgame.games(year=2015, week=[7, 8])
players = nflgame.combine_game_stats(games)
for player in players:
    print player, player.formatted_stats()
```

> should i be using nfldb?
You don't have to, but you can:
```python
import nfldb
db = nfldb.connect()
q = nfldb.Query(db)
q.game(season_year=2015, season_type='Regular')

for pp in q.as_aggregate():
    print pp.player, pp
```",{},,User,False
