2686,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-23 18:09:46+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,136959,Mottie,,,96857668,124190452,"Hi @aeryn21!

I think the issue might be that the css needs to include the unique IDs as well.

```css
#colSelect18:checked + label {
    background: #5797d7;
    border-color: #555;
}
#colSelect18:checked ~ #columnSelector18 {
    display: block;
}
```

I set up that demo to use only css for the popup, you might be better off using jQuery to add/remove a class name to make the popup visible.

Also, you don't need to include that `textExtraction` function because you can change the [`textAttribute` option](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#textattribute) (default is `""data-text""`) to match your extra data:

```js
$(function() {
	$(""#tablesorterMotorchart18"").tablesorter({
		widgets: ['zebra', 'columnSelector', 'filter'],
		textAttribute: 'sortvalue',
		headers: {
			//'.products_id': {filter: false, sortInitialOrder: ""desc"" },
			//'.products_buy': {filter: false, sorter: false}
			7: {sorter: false, filter: false}
		},
		widgetOptions : {
			columnSelector_container : $('#columnSelector18')
		}
	});
}); // end document.ready
```

I removed the options that were already set as their default value",{},,User,False
