2982,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-18 12:39:02+00:00,6794278,scanny/python-pptx,9824166,realtimecarsten,,,266289892,337576738,"I hope this example shows what I would like to achieve and what the problem is. I would like to have the typesetting like the last bullet (with the italic and non-italic words), but with a soft break after the colon (like in the first two bullets). However, using a run I get an extra bullet instead (bullet 3+4). See also comments in my code.

![text-vs-run-problem](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9824166/31718790-6e8270ea-b411-11e7-8054-4584d46ac9b3.png)

A nice way would be if one could add a soft break at the end of the run (here: the one with "" something:"").

So here's the code for the example:

<pre>
from pptx import Presentation

prs = Presentation()

bullet_layout = prs.slide_layouts[1]
slide = prs.slides.add_slide(bullet_layout)
title_shape = slide.shapes.title
body_shape = slide.shapes.placeholders[1]
title_shape.text = ""Example\nNo. 1""

# embedded \n in string with text_frame.text gives you a soft break
body_shape.text_frame.text = ""To emphasize something:\nUse italics.""

# repeat, just to see it happens also with other paragraphs
p = body_shape.text_frame.add_paragraph()
p.text = ""To emphasize something:\nUse italics.""
 
# using a run, no soft break, but a new bullet instead
p = body_shape.text_frame.add_paragraph()
r = p.add_run()
r.text = ""To emphasize something:\nUse italics.""

# and this is an example how I would like to format the text, but with the soft breaks (which I cannot get done)
p = body_shape.text_frame.add_paragraph()
r = p.add_run()
r.text = ""To ""
r = p.add_run()
r.text = ""emphasize"" 
r.font.italic = True
r = p.add_run()
r.text = "" something: Use ""
r = p.add_run()
r.text = ""italics.""
r.font.italic = True
 
prs.save(""softBreak.pptx"")
</pre>

",{},NONE,User,False
2984,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-03 01:17:31+00:00,6794278,scanny/python-pptx,2062718,scanny,,,310561475,378097117,"k, got it, thanks.

I've put in the fix in the main code, it will be out with the next release in a month or so.

In the meantime, if you can run a local version, make the `validate_int()` method in `pptx.oxml.simpletypes` line 39 look like this:

```python
@classmethod
def validate_int(cls, value):
