3028,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-02 07:33:00+00:00,8292338,ultrabug/py3status,474389,ultrabug,,,137615048,191110947,"Hi @nschubach 

First of all, just so it's clear, all the modules listed by `py3status modules list` really are available to you. There's nothing more to install.

As far as I see it, the main reason is that you missed the underscore in the order and config of `mpd_status`. Here is an example of my working setup:

```
order += ""mpd_status trotrobox""

mpd_status trotrobox {
	cache_timeout = 15
	color = ""true""
	format = ""{name}|{artist}""
	max_width = 50
	host = 'trotrobox'
	port = 1337
	on_click 1 = ""exec mpc -h trotrobox -p 1337 toggle""
	on_click 2 = ""exec mpc -h trotrobox -p 1337 prev""
	on_click 3 = ""exec mpc -h trotrobox -p 1337 next""
	on_click 4 = ""exec mpc -h trotrobox -p 1337 volume +20""
	on_click 5 = ""exec mpc -h trotrobox -p 1337 volume -20""
}
```

And yes, you have to install any dependency listed on the modules' doc before using it. For the mpd_status one, it's `python-mpd2` which should be listed if you run a `pip freeze` on your machine.

Also note that you can get all modules' documentation by running `py3status modules details` or going to this page : https://github.com/ultrabug/py3status/blob/master/py3status/modules/README.md

Finally, feel free to come over on FreeNode IRC channel #py3status if you wish !

Hope this helps :)",{},,User,False
