4049,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-14 09:32:02+00:00,6054289,niklasf/python-chess,1834123,ddugovic,,,154831189,219210569,"This is an open problem, as chess has not yet been solved; however, there are two factors to consider:

1.  Programs like ChessMaster, Fritz, etc. start analysis from the end of a game and work backwards, reusing cached evaluations.
2.  Stockfish and other engines have time management for playing a game from start to finish, the same way that human chess players are familiar with time management.  It's not entirely clear what the best way to allocate time for analysis (from finish to start of a game) is.",{},,User,False
