4422,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-17 14:27:35+00:00,52575367,nficano/python-lambda,13487891,jmeekhof,,,250954986,323090073,"Yes, I've run into this type of issue before. You have 2 issues. 

1. Your c extension must be compiled for Amazon linux. There are 2 ways to solve this. 
a. spin up an ec2 instance and deploy from there.
b. create a docker container and develop and deploy from the container.(this is how I do it) Here's a quick and dirty Dockerfile: https://gist.github.com/jmeekhof/f226a8e148f345c71e8c0f87123ee8bf

2. Your second issue is you need to be able to deploy your compiled object with your lambda function. Right now, this project doesn't have a way to automate the additional objects.  Your best workaround is to `lambda build` and then using a zip utility add the necessary shared libraries, and manually deploy. Here's a good write up on this process: http://www.perrygeo.com/running-python-with-compiled-code-on-aws-lambda.html",{},,User,False
