4499,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-04 18:50:08+00:00,131902678,shosca/django-sorcery,260210,shosca,,,338259565,402542309,"> none of the subcommands will appear in djangos

True, but i don't like to litter the `./manage.py -h` list, its gets really wild when you start adding apps with commands, would rather namespace commands.

> help will need to enumerate all subcommands:

Fixed it
```
$ pipenv run ./manage.py sorcery -h
Loading .env environment variables...
usage: manage.py sorcery [-h] createall dropall

django-sorcery management commands

positional arguments:
  createall   Creates SQLAlchemy database schemas
  dropall     Drops SQLAlchemy database schemas

optional arguments:
  -h, --help  show this help message and exit
```
> not a fan of not following django philosophy for the way they do commands

[zen of python](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0020/) says `Namespaces are one honking great idea -- let's do more of those!` :trollface: 

",{},OWNER,User,False
