4875,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-10 08:20:35+00:00,30379674,adamchainz/django-mysql,857609,adamchainz,,,272840151,343406392,"You can always use https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.11/ref/settings/#std:setting-SILENCED_SYSTEM_CHECKS to silence a system check that you know better than.

However I agree the logic is a bit inverted and we should be check if *at least one* connection is MySQL 5.7+ not that all MySQL connections are 5.7+ :)

It looks to me like this is the only change needed for that:

```patch
diff --git a/django_mysql/models/fields/json.py b/django_mysql/models/fields/json.py
index fbce9ba..84ff376 100644
--- a/django_mysql/models/fields/json.py
+++ b/django_mysql/models/fields/json.py
@@ -58,15 +58,16 @@ class JSONField(Field):
     def _check_mysql_version(self):
         errors = []

-        any_conn_works = True
+        any_conn_works = False
         conn_names = ['default'] + list(set(connections) - {'default'})
         for db in conn_names:
             conn = connections[db]
             if (
                 hasattr(conn, 'mysql_version') and
-                (connection_is_mariadb(conn) or conn.mysql_version < (5, 7))
+                not connection_is_mariadb(conn) and
+                conn.mysql_version >= (5, 7)
             ):
-                any_conn_works = False
+                any_conn_works = True

         if not any_conn_works:
             errors.append(
```",{},OWNER,User,False
