4982,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-07 20:38:05+00:00,36964309,jantman/awslimitchecker,273454,jantman,,,180115744,252355262,"Correct, ``--profile`` isn't a supported option. awslimitchecker does not use aws cli, it uses [boto3](http://boto3.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) to interface with the AWS API.

If you wish to use a profile from your ``~/.aws/credentials`` file, you can do so with the ``AWS_PROFILE`` environment variable, per the [boto credentials documentation](http://boto3.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guide/configuration.html#environment-variable-configuration).",{},,User,False
4984,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-02 10:48:45+00:00,36964309,jantman/awslimitchecker,273454,jantman,,,153766161,244344160,"Ok, this was merged to botocore master in https://github.com/boto/botocore/commit/c3babf30df041ff064882f5779b96e1eeb1e4886 and released last night as [1.4.51](https://github.com/boto/botocore/blob/1.4.51/CHANGELOG.rst).

At the very least, we should get more-helpful exception messages that clearly show when requests have been retried but reached the maximum number of retries.

Beyond that, I'm not sure what I can really do. I'm going to close this issue; please see my [comment above](https://github.com/jantman/awslimitchecker/issues/187#issuecomment-220777272) for some possible solutions.",{},,User,False
