5421,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-27 02:01:25+00:00,8528872,JohannesBuchner/imagehash,51015,JohannesBuchner,,,185551612,256526885,"Hi @bjlittle,

This pull-request contains several independent things and should be split up.

I think you are trying to do the testing foremost, so lets focus on that first, and move the other changes to another PR.

setup.py is getting too complicated, please keep it simple. We have one file, and one package, there is no reason to write parsing functions. Lets just keep the version in setup.py. I am ok with adding six as a dependency (is it possible to separate testing dependencies and install dependencies?).

> To allow the tests to run without an internet connection, I've banked your lovely Alyson Hannigan test image within the repo
That test image was used in one of the blog posts from which I started. I don't think you have the right to redistribute the image.

I think we discussed not changing the code style. Please remove such changes from this PR. We may later think about formalising a Codestyle check. To be honest I think this is overkill for this tiny project.

> Can I convince you to adopt a pep440 styple of versioning your code?
You can change the version in setup.py to -dev if you need to separate the pypi package from your current development version.

> As you might be able to tell from travis-ci, using the PR, imagehash is running in python2.7, python3.4 and python3.5! 
Great! Do you have a link of travis-ci testing against your fork?",{},,User,False
