5584,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-24 13:03:33+00:00,13839795,ionelmc/python-redis-lock,9401434,BigBorg,,,276567178,346824312,"No, only content inside {} bracket is used to generate hash slot. If you use  {lock}resource and {lock-signal}resource, they might end up in different slot since hash result of ""lock"" and ""lock-signal"" is different. But if you use lock:{resource} and lock-signal:{resource}, the two keys for the same resource will end up in the same slot. Also, since resource differs, this will spread out lock and lock-signal keys for different resources which is the purpose of Redis Cluster ( to shard content ). ",{},NONE,User,False
