5886,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-10 15:36:45+00:00,39518221,kbytesys/django-recaptcha2,4700618,pymarco,,,249054787,321588659,"Thank you for responding.

For posterity, the problem was with [certifi](https://github.com/certifi/python-certifi) failing to validate ""cross-signed certificates"". My solution was to remove `certifi`. I also downgraded `requests` to match the version on my dev environment.

Recaptcha is now working in production.

Here's the [relevant issue](https://github.com/certifi/python-certifi/issues/26) for certifi.

----
To track down the problem, I added a catch all logger

    LOGGING = {
        'version': 1,
        'disable_existing_loggers': False,

        'filters': {
            'require_debug_false': {
                '()': 'django.utils.log.RequireDebugFalse'
            }
        },

        'handlers': {
            'mail_admins': {
                'level': 'ERROR',
                'filters': ['require_debug_false'],
                'class': 'django.utils.log.AdminEmailHandler'
            },

            'error_logfile': {
                'level': 'ERROR',
                'filters': ['require_debug_false'],
                'class': 'logging.FileHandler',
                'filename': Path(PROJECT_DIR, ""logs/errors.log""),
            },
        },

        'loggers': {
            'django.request': {
                'handlers': ['mail_admins'],
                'level': 'ERROR',
                'propagate': True,
            },

            '': {
                'handlers': ['error_logfile'],
                'level': 'ERROR',
            },
        }
    }

The log included the following error:

    SSLError: [SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] certificate verify failed (_ssl.c:579)

