6391,IssueCommentEvent,2015-03-06 21:05:36+00:00,10674033,marcgibbons/django-rest-swagger,842452,ariovistus,,,60071223,77635631,"I see no reason why this should be expected behavior. The html is generated by swagger (which you should probably leave alone) based on data sent to it by the django-rest-swagger apis.

a cursory look through the source suggests DRS isn't explicitly passing true,false,null to swagger, so I'd guess swagger is automatically generating these based on the type. Don't know if there is a supported way to override, but if there is, build_form_parameters in introspectors.py is a good place to start looking. [swagger spec 1.2](https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-spec/blob/master/versions/1.2.md) is another.",{},,User,False
