6742,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-04 10:28:53+00:00,27609645,web2py/pydal,1794396,nextghost,33118,web2py,172710275,244595096,"Adapter refactoring should be complete. There are some FIXMEs in the changeset that you should review and fix later (fixing the one about name conflicts will probably break existing third-party code). The new code for passing parent scope tables to subqueries through expression trees isn't pretty but since the whole thing is up for a major redesign anyway, it'll do for now.

Summary of internal changes: Many adapter methods that originally accepted/returned table names now accept/return table objects. However, some code still uses the `self.db[tablename]` anti-pattern when it should pass the table object around directly.

In addition to the usual `select()` parameters, the `nested_select()` method also accepts a new parameter `correlated` which defaults to `True`. If set to `False`, the subquery will never reference any tables from the parent scope. Otherwise tables will be resolved in this order: 1) tables appearing in `left` or `join` arguments; 2) tables from parent scope; 3) tables appearing in `query` or `fields` arguments.

Note that the FROM clause may become empty as a result. That is perfectly valid SQL syntax but not currently supported by PyDAL. If you want to have the same table in the FROM clause of both the parent query and the subquery while allowing references to parent scope, you'll have to use unique aliases.

All that's left for me to do is to write unit tests. If you have any further suggestions for this PR, now's your last chance.",{},,User,False
