6786,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-12 19:08:58+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,4902813,thomelane,47359,apache,269622618,404618938,"Assuming you're asking about variable batch sizes for the input, you should take a look at [`Module.reshape`](https://mxnet.incubator.apache.org/api/python/module/module.html#mxnet.module.Module.reshape) for this. Some related discussion can be found at https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/issues/2294. And based on the unit-test, an example of its usage would be:

```
x = mx.sym.Variable('x')
y = mx.sym.FullyConnected(x, num_hidden=4)

exe = y.simple_bind(mx.cpu(), x=(5,4))
exe.arg_arrays[0][:] = 1
exe.arg_arrays[1][:] = mx.nd.ones((4,4))
exe.arg_arrays[2][:] = 0

new_exe = exe.reshape(x=(3,4))
new_exe.forward(is_train=False)

new_exe.outputs[0].asnumpy()
```

Also note that with Gluon, you can call `Block`s with different sized batches without having to manage reshapes, etc.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
