6878,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-24 15:59:02+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,11234557,cjolivier01,47359,apache,308164189,375901906,"I was thinking about this last night and I think I can come up with a more elegant solution. However, I would prefer not to directly overwrite the bulk size variable because:
1) The whole save/restore thing the way it is done now doesn't seem very thread-safe (or multi-graph safe) since there's only one engine, but possibly many graphs, so there seems to be some disconnect here that may need to be dealt with one day (although it's currently not a problem).  Please correct me if I am wrong here.
2) If profiler sets bulk size to zero, then saves the old value and something else wants to set the bulk size (ie from python), it will both overwrite the 0 set by the profiler and also, when the aggregate is turned off, it will replace the older pre-python-set value.  Because of this, you won;t be able to toggle aggregate or profiling without possibly affecting the deterministic behavior of the *intended* bulk size value",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
