The management command will, for each summary signature that has `subtest_signatures` in extra_properties:

* Get the signature ids for all the subtests and add them to the subtests for that series
* Rewrite the extra_properties section to remove 'subtest_signatures'

I *think* that should be all that's needed. We also need to verify that the etl code will automatically convert old signatures as it encounters them, since we'll continue to be processing date before this script finishes. I think it should work, but we should double check. You can test this by backing up to an earlier version, ingesting one or two pushes with talos data, then migrating to this version and ingesting one or two pushes with the same data. Then verify that the signatures are what you'd expect (all subtest information still there, etc).",{},,User,False
