7623,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-31 10:48:33+00:00,14993021,ipython/traitlets,501585,ankostis,230453,ipython,204140838,276331790,"Regarding the return value (`app` or `start()` results):

If it returns `app`, you still loose any `start()` results the first time you invoke the `launch_instance()`.
Then you can re-invoke `start()` to get the its return values.  But that's not symmetrical.

Since I faced the exact same question in my code, I crafted a new class-method that instanciate + initialize app, and returns it, without invoking `start()` on it.

Anyhow, fixing this issue, I would return the `start()` values from `launch_instance()`.",{},,User,False
