7791,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-30 05:51:16+00:00,648332,assimp/assimp,6587734,AntiMoron,265533,assimp,156464246,222416236,"@kimkulling  Hi, it's been days and I get an obj model file which sizes 3MB.

When try to open it with SimpleAssimpViewX (the sample project cmake generates), it always fail.
And I try to log out the error message it complains:
 ```SimpleAssimpViewX[65668:5287914] : OBJ-file is too small.```
After I check into [assimp code](https://github.com/assimp/assimp/blob/6b243230b29d14e778563f2855164f172a00ca77/code/ObjFileImporter.cpp). I found that the ObjMinSize is 16 bytes. The code that trigger this exception is as follows.

```c++
void ObjFileImporter::InternReadFile( const std::string &file, aiScene* pScene, IOSystem* pIOHandler) {
    // Read file into memory
    static const std::string mode = ""rb"";
    std::unique_ptr<IOStream> fileStream( pIOHandler->Open( file, mode));
    if( !fileStream.get() ) {
        throw DeadlyImportError( ""Failed to open file "" + file + ""."" );
    }

    // Get the file-size and validate it, throwing an exception when fails
    size_t fileSize = fileStream->FileSize();
    if( fileSize < ObjMinSize ) {
        throw DeadlyImportError( ""OBJ-file is too small."");
    }
```

I guess there's something wrong with the implementation for OS X. If so, it's no wonder FBX files can't be imported correctly.",{},,User,False
