7906,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-01 07:44:29+00:00,744916,gem/oq-engine,2463856,micheles,316546,gem,152951553,244001701,"Additional notes: after lots of experiments I discovered that using variable-length arrays (the new feature of h5py) is not more efficient than using different datasets. Also, using too many datasets is not efficient. So the best strategy is to use a dataset per each site and to store the data for all realizations, IMTs and events in a compact format, which is efficient both in reading and writing. The array can then be reordered on the workers, working by bunch of sites.",{},,User,False
