8206,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-15 10:14:50+00:00,15169689,vmware/pyvmomi,13127297,prziborowski,473334,vmware,207751879,279970732,"With the managed object, you can typically call Destroy method on it to delete it.
Note for a datacenter, it will unmanage any hosts under it.

If you want an example by supplying the name, you could try the following.
I'm copying quite a bit from datacenter.py.
```
from pyVim.task import WaitForTask
from pyVim.connect import SmartConnect, Disconnect
import cli
PARSER = cli.build_arg_parser()
PARSER.add_argument(""-n"", ""--name"",
                    required=True,
                    action=""store"",
                    help=""Name of the Datacenter to create."")
MY_ARGS = PARSER.parse_args()
cli.prompt_for_password(MY_ARGS)
SI = SmartConnect(host=MY_ARGS.host,
                  user=MY_ARGS.user,
                  pwd=MY_ARGS.password,
                  port=MY_ARGS.port)
rootFolder = SI.content.rootFolder
for dc in rootFolder.childEntity:
   if dc.name == MY_ARGS.name:
      WaitForTask(dc.Destroy())
      break
Disconnect(SI)

```
",{},,User,False
