8805,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-11 19:43:56+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,8816362,rueberger,779641,Parsely,340072814,404287755,"Ah, thanks for working through this with me, that did the trick. 

Where my internal model was going wrong was that I was putting the split between initialization and step in the wrong place. 

As 

```python
client = KafkaClient(hosts=""xxxxxxx"")
topic = client.topics['mytopic']
consumer = topic.get_simple_consumer(
    auto_offset_reset=OffsetType.LATEST,
    reset_offset_on_start=True)
LAST_N_MESSAGES = 1

def consume_latest()
    offsets = [(p, op.next_offset - LAST_N_MESSAGES - 1) for p, op in consumer._partitions.iteritems()]
    consumer.reset_offsets(offsets)
     return consumer.consume()
```

instead of 

```python
client = KafkaClient(hosts=""xxxxxxx"")
topic = client.topics['mytopic']
LAST_N_MESSAGES = 1

def consume_latest()
    consumer = topic.get_simple_consumer(
        auto_offset_reset=OffsetType.LATEST,
        reset_offset_on_start=True
    )
    offsets = [(p, op.next_offset - LAST_N_MESSAGES - 1) for p, op in consumer._partitions.iteritems()]
    consumer.reset_offsets(offsets)
     return consumer.consume()
```
(the extra -1 compensates for `op.next_offset` being current offset + 1)

The latter does what I want (just tested). 

I guess my hang up was not treating `SimpleConsumer`s as ephemeral. They are ephemeral, right? Initialization is cheap?  

My two cents on docs: I think some simple examples that step through common operations with a nice diagram showing topic contents and consumer offset pointers would work wonders in illustrating basic `kafka` mechanics and  `pykafka` usage. Whether this would be widely useful I think would depend on what the use case for typical users of `pykafka` are. For the time-being, my use cases are relatively simple (single partitions only), which uses such a small subset of `kafka`'s full complexity that I had a hard time finding what I wanted to know at a glance from `kafka`'s ponderous docs. ",{},NONE,User,False
