9277,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-19 14:18:13+00:00,62899021,openwisp/django-x509,203964,hggh,1150243,openwisp,258830525,330554572,"The Serializer of the REST Frameworks uses Model.objects.create()

Inside the objects.create method from Django ""force_insert"" will be set to True. So our save is called with kwargs ""force_insert=True"". For the first super save() calling it is fine.

But we call super save() again with force_insert=True. The entry has already a PK so the IntegrityError is thrown by the database.

Adding a ""kwargs['force_insert'] = False"" before the second super save() call seems to fixes the problem.

