10020,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-19 17:32:04+00:00,34906350,BlueBrain/NeuroM,675013,juanchopanza,1479142,BlueBrain,133286915,186317397,"Maybe I can clarify the two of the main issues:

1. Not general: as far as I can see, this is a very specific test on two populations. it is not a universal validation (there is no such thing), it is just a set of statistical tests chosen for a specific purpose. This could be made more general for example by allowing the user to select what kind of test they want to perform.

2. Code quality. I think there is agreement on this.

If we can make an application after fixing 1. and 2. then `neurom` is the right place for it. Otherwise, it should go elsewhere. But I really can't see why this is a problem at this stage. If we need something for M30, then we put whatever we have an internal repository used for morphology validations. If somebody outside of BBP needs it, then we can thing of providing it as an example. Bear in mind that applications used in the task service are tied to the release cycle of NeuroM and we won't be making a release every time some script gets modified. So it is good to have M30 scripts de-coupled from the NeuroM release cycle anyway.",{},,User,False
