10569,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-24 17:12:55+00:00,15510254,openfisca/openfisca-core,11834997,fpagnoux,1794404,openfisca,230833041,303790594,"Good point 👍 .
It's indeed better to keep the parallelism business out of the core if we can.
I found an alternative implementation.

I still need the `--nose` option though. This options allows me to run OpenFisca YAML tests cases with nose (CI-friendly output, no failfast) without a boilerplate `test_yaml.py`. This has two advantages:
- Less boilerplate
- More important, I can do `openfisca-run-test --nose fileA.yaml fileB.yaml path/to/file.yaml`. This allows me to [rely on Circle CI native parallelism features](https://github.com/openfisca/openfisca-france/blob/circle-parallel/circle.yml#L22).",{},,User,False
