10781,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-28 22:24:48+00:00,111010291,aws/sagemaker-spark,5501191,andremoeller,2232217,aws,284998340,354367414,"Hi @marami52 ,

Thanks for using Amazon SageMaker!

Instead of using a `SparkContext`, I think we should be using a `SparkSession` to load the data into a `DataFrame`, like:

```
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
spark = SparkSession.builder.config(""spark.driver.extraClassPath"", "":"".join(sagemaker_pyspark.classpath_jars())).getOrCreate()
training_data = spark.read.format(""libsvm"").option(""numFeatures"", ""784"")
  .load(""s3a://sagemaker-sample-data-{}/spark/mnist/train/"".format(region))
```

We have this wrong in our docs -- I'll be sure to get this updated.

Thanks again!",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
