10799,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-15 21:32:18+00:00,81612762,trailofbits/manticore,2467355,mossberg,2314423,trailofbits,239314074,322595834,"summarizing chat discussion:

We are considering removing the need for a `BinaryView` (e.g https://github.com/trailofbits/manticore/blob/31c7dc67834e0996b872d0a07ef049961078aaab/manticore/platforms/linux.py#L2091). Currently we only use it because ""binja is buggy in telling us which flags are affected by an instruction"".

This is illustrated here:

https://github.com/trailofbits/manticore/blob/31c7dc67834e0996b872d0a07ef049961078aaab/manticore/core/cpu/binja.py#L1110-L1118

The commented out code shows using the `Architecture` to get the modified flags, which does not require a `BinaryView`. However, there is a bug and the `flags_written_by_flag_write_type` API does not work correctly. This behavior can be achieved equivalently through using a `BinaryView`, using a `Function` (`cpu.disasm.current_func`), which is what we do instead.

If we removed the `BinaryView`, we would need to ""hardcode the flags affected for each instruction"".",{},,User,False
