10827,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-07 09:17:13+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,154475,redpony,2374376,clab,279947629,349908648,"That's a strange error for a recent computer to have! (Basically, it means
the processor has SIMD vector registers but doesn't have a tanh function.
Or at least the compiler thinks it doesn't.) If you're running on ""normal
hardware"" (not exotically cheap or something), this probably means the OS
was installed badly (i.e., it's a bad image or something).

But, I pushed what I think is a fix so it should compile.

