11182,IssueCommentEvent,2015-06-17 11:42:41+00:00,11031844,uqfoundation/dill,321534,mmckerns,2855931,uqfoundation,88855877,112763195,"You mean this, right? https://github.com/celery/celery/issues/2526

If you just do `import dill`, that should bootstrap all of the `dill` types into the pickle registry.  (This was broken for the last few months, unbeknownst to me, but I just recently fixed it here: https://github.com/uqfoundation/dill/issues/107).  `dill` can inject types into the `pickle` registry, but not the `cPickle` registry.  The point being, if `celery` is calling `pickle.load`, it might not be calling a `dill` `Unpickler` (which is required in some cases) -- or if you are not doing an `import dill` and you are using `pickle` to unpickle, then you might also see failure.",{},,User,False
11184,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-10 18:37:56+00:00,11031844,uqfoundation/dill,1771820,irmen,2855931,uqfoundation,308428990,380204707,"My $0.02: don't support Python releases that have reached EOL. People that still run these should be able to pin an older compatible dill version in their projects, anyway.   What 'EOL' means can be difficult, the official EOL date from python.org may not be the same as say, a linux distribution's EOL date...",{},NONE,User,False
