11429,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-25 06:43:43+00:00,22072746,pantsbuild/pex,28559461,bjorn-spire,3065172,pantsbuild,194327218,407650863,"One of my colleagues figured out if you empty the module list and try to import the package again it'll work. So we came up with this hack that has helped us work around it:

```python
# This seems to be sufficient to fix my import problems.
# If this happens to work outside of this project, we'll move it to commons
import sys

for _ in range(5):
    try:
        import google
        import google.cloud
        import google.cloud.bigquery
        break
    except (ModuleNotFoundError, ImportError):
        print('BQ Import hack triggered! retrying')
        for module in list(sys.modules):
            if module.startswith('google'):
                del sys.modules[module]
else:
    raise ImportError('BQ Import hack failed')

# If we reach this, the hack must've worked.
from google.cloud import bigquery
```

So wherever we need the bigquery library we do `from spire.commons.bigquery.import_hack import bigquery`",{},NONE,User,False
