11493,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-04 19:38:11+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,130433740,180017547,"Ok, I think I see a great way to restore the checking from #2525.

There are many types of values produced and consumed within the graph, many of which would not be useful to show to users. But, luckily, we have a symbol table that indicates which values a user could possibly have included!

The idea would be to restore the graph checks from #2525 between values that a user could have specified: in particular, between a Node with an `Address` product, and a task with partially consumed inputs in which one of the missing values is registered in the `SymbolTable`.",{},,User,False
