11912,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-14 04:56:47+00:00,14991049,nccgroup/Scout2,751555,l01cd3v,4067082,nccgroup,272539438,351608973,"I pushed some code on branch `issue209` to provide a proof of concept - I think I like how this works as it does not require to modify the rules, but rather allows to add conditions in the ruleset and create multiple versions of each rule.

If this works for you, then you'd just have to change all of the ec2-security-group-rules that you care for in the detailed.json ruleset, using the example below. If you happen to do so, I'd gladly accept a PR :) 

```
diff AWSScout2/rules/data/rulesets/default.json  AWSScout2/rules/data/rulesets/detailed.json 
187c187,200
<                 ""level"": ""danger""
---
>                 ""versions"": {
>                     ""in_use"": {
>                         ""conditions"": [
>                             [ ""_INCLUDE_(conditions/ec2-security-group-in-use.json)"", """", """" ]
>                         ],
>                         ""level"": ""danger""
>                     },
>                     ""not_used"": {
>                         ""conditions"": [
>                             [ ""_INCLUDE_(conditions/ec2-security-group-not-used.json)"", """", """" ]
>                         ],
>                         ""level"": ""warning""
>                     }
>                 }
```

",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
