12164,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-21 17:21:43+00:00,10247874,docker/docker-py,10620046,GordonTheTurtle,5429470,docker,209214438,281413255,"<!-- AUTOMATED:POULE:DCO-EXPLANATION -->
Please sign your commits following these rules:
https://github.com/docker/docker/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#sign-your-work
The easiest way to do this is to amend the last commit:
~~~console
$ git clone -b ""event-http-headers"" git@github.com:Anvil/docker-py.git somewhere
$ cd somewhere
$ git rebase -i HEAD~842354516384
editor opens
change each 'pick' to 'edit'
save the file and quit
$ git commit --amend -s --no-edit
$ git rebase --continue # and repeat the amend for each commit
$ git push -f
~~~

Amending updates the existing PR. You **DO NOT** need to open a new one.
",{},,User,False
