12551,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-11 20:34:17+00:00,22757589,freelawproject/juriscraper,236970,mlissner,6012898,freelawproject,199958349,271985970,"`date_filed` is only on the `OpinionSite`, not on the other objects that override `AbstractSite`, so we'll want to put it there, not on `AbstrictSite`, where it would get inherited by oral arguments and other things in the future.

The other thing that needs to happen is that the new field needs to be added to the `_req_attrs` attribute on `OpinionSite`. By adding it there we make sure that it gets processed by the `parse` method.

I think the return `[False] * len(self.case_names)` should work. I'm not sure if doing `* len(self.cases)` would work. Maybe?

The DB side of things is all taken care of in CL as of a moment ago.",{},,User,False
