12599,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-22 21:39:10+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,1821014,krancour,6117407,deis,96585700,123874553,"Also wanted to add I'm not totally in favor of the `RequireOverride=` hack.  As I understand it, CoreOS, by convention, runs etcd 2.0.x as `etcd2.service` so that users can (easily) choose to run either that or legacy 0.4.x-- which is simple `etcd.service.`  We could choose, near-term, to defy that convention and simply run our containerized etcd 2.0.x _as_ `etcd.service`, thereby requiring very few other changes-- some of which would have the potential to complicate the upgrade path as noted in some previous comments.  When we hit Deis 2.0 and breaking changes are expected, we could step back in line with the convention of running etcd 2.0.x _as_ `etcd2.service` at that time.",{},,User,False
