12647,IssueCommentEvent,2015-06-01 23:35:11+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,597920,wenzowski,6117407,deis,82065798,107747079,"Thanks for the offer @LinuxJedi Yes, I understood Maxim was probably suggesting a hash of the remote_addr as a way to avoid the emptystring problem, which wasn't what I was trying to request. In the case where affinity is only necessary if a GET variable is set, like this one, the roundtrip to memcached could be avoided entirely when an emptystring is encountered if affinity is not needed for these requests by falling back to round robin for these requests. Having ngninx/memcached hash a pseudo-random number seems like unnecessary overhead for the requests that do not require affinity. I don't know the nginx internals very well though, so I understand the wontfix is probably for a good reason.",{},,User,False
