12673,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-03 04:32:17+00:00,107710074,Microsoft/vsts-python-api,20437699,karann-jain,6154722,Microsoft,318898662,386188998,"@tedchamb I think i found the root cause of above exceptions, appears like the order of attributes in the request changes every time client library parses the response and the exceptions are thrown for the last attribute. Which is either environments, id or name. if these are on the top of the request there is no issue, request is successfully processed.

However, when i directly call the vsts api, i see the order of response is always the same, I think client library is somehow changing the order of the response and the same i am sending it back (as per the sample above) which is causing parsing failure on vsts api.

