12703,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-12 19:40:02+00:00,5196969,chardet/chardet,976345,dan-blanchard,6211498,chardet,221273124,293685493,"> str.encode/str.decode can trigger imports. Delayed imports in a web application can cause deadlocks in acquiring the import lock on certain versions of Python. Requests already has had this problem and I'd rather not add it to chardet.

I know about the import triggering, but not the deadlocks. The tricky bit there though is that typically people are using chardet so that they can call `bytes.decode` and process the file, so they're going to end up importing the same thing anyway.

> I believe we can return all of our most confident detections. We can provide an extra function to users to do this for them, but I don't think we should do it as part of detect.

#111 was just opened yesterday to add exactly that. I just need to review it.",{},,User,False
