12710,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-06 17:43:20+00:00,71996613,blue-yonder/tsfresh,389874,jneuff,6234170,blue-yonder,198513955,270959517,"1. The class inherits from dictionary. It seemed odd to me too at first. It's just a way to do the setup. I don't know what the most pythonic way would be. But I do think we could improve the naming. Why not call it ExtractionSettings? The prefix feature seems redundant to me. Also the named parameters could be called extraction_settings.
2. I think reasonable is a better name than smart. But maybe we can come up with something better. The name should reflect the fact that it calculates most features but is way faster than to calculate all features.
4. The module default.py is needed as the default settings are accessed from various functions and we should have them in one place. It is not intended to be changed by the user. To change the settings one can set the named parameters.
5. This TODO has been there for quite a while. We could change the parameter's name of course while we're busy breaking things. I would just leave it. But now is probably a good time to remove the TODO.
6. We should definitely have two dictionaries. It's way easier to handle if you want to have the same settings for several kinds and just alter the settings for one kind.

We could just take care of the remaining points in this branch and then merge the pr into master. I don't see why we should open another branch.

Regarding the reporting: In my opinion it wasn't flexible enough this way. It's better to get rid of it now than having to stick with it. We should rather aim to make more internal information available as proposed in PR #87 .


Remaining points we need to tackle:

- Typos in the docs (Where?)
- The notebooks have yet to be updated
- Change some of the names (Which?)
- Remove the TODO mentioned in point 5 above",{},,User,False
