12763,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-15 18:09:38+00:00,77478378,ethereum/py-evm,824194,pipermerriam,6250754,ethereum,348118454,413285134,"@eddybenkhin to expand on what @carver said.

When we import a block which **does not** cause a re-org, i.e. it is part of a different fork and the block being imported doesn't score higher than the current `HEAD` block, we want all things in the import to succeed **except** for it should be skipping/bypassing any logic that sets things as *canonical*.  Then, at the point where you import the block which causes the minority fork to score higher than the current head, all of the setting of things as canonical should happen then.  It would be expected behavior for the import to result in the block **not** being part of the chain, however, if you are getting an error during import then we may need to fix something.",{},MEMBER,User,False
