12858,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-03 17:39:55+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1418419,kalefranz,6392739,conda,211749706,284019927,"Honestly, I'm stumped at the moment.  I'm wondering if it has something to do with `/usr/people/kirk/miniconda3/bin/conda` being the executable of the active process, which is being replaced.  If that's the case, I've never seen it before on Linux.

