This is also confirmation that the transactional rollback is working at least.  For a conda version before 4.3, you would have just been left with a completely borked conda.

I honestly don't know what's going on yet though...

If I were on your system myself, line 241 in `/usr/people/kirk/miniconda3/lib/python3.5/site-packages/conda/gateways/disk/create.py`, I would replace with

```
try:
    shutil.copy2(src, dst)
except Exception as e:
