12909,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-21 03:15:43+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,57394,fperez,6392739,conda,178668617,268424148,"@kalefranz, it happened again on my freshly installed miniconda :(

I've updated to conda 4.3.1 from conda-canary and uploaded a [full log here](https://gist.github.com/fperez/d9bc27bb0f1bd0faeb246888bc033263), I hope that gives you something to work with.

I've also [uploaded here](http://fperez.org/tmp/conda.tgz) a tarball of my entire conda directory, which I keep at `~/usr/conda`, for you to play with.  I hope this helps you replicate the problem, and thanks for any help you can provide.  This particular bug has really been a thorn on my side over the last few months, as every time it hits me, my only option is to delete my entire conda installation and start from scratch.

BTW, if in the meantime you have any tips on possible workarounds, I'd love to hear.  Since my current solution is so disruptive, even a temporary band-aid would be good to know about.

And thanks again for your persistent help!",{},,User,False
12910,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-30 10:58:45+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1042804,mingwandroid,6392739,conda,253729320,340410711,"I believe I have fixed this and would appreciate your feedback.

From Linux, macOS or MSYS2/Git-for-Windows/Cygwin:

```
CONDA_AUTO_UPDATE_CONDA=False conda install -c c3i_test2 pycosat
```

From Windows cmd.exe:

```
set CONDA_AUTO_UPDATE_CONDA=False
conda install -c c3i_test2 pycosat
```
",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
