12943,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-01 01:16:05+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,38393,msarahan,6392739,conda,37908864,204197749,"Yes, that's the plan, anyway.  The installers will be modified to give you 3 options instead of 2:

1. add conda/bin to PATH (old way)
2. add conda/exec to PATH (new folder, contains only activate and conda as symlinks to those in the bin folder)
3. Do not change PATH

This will be released as conda 4.1, and installers for miniconda should come some time after that.  Anaconda installers will get it later - we just had a release, so the next one will be in about 3 months.

Sorry about the symlink - I can see the other side, though.  I haven't been successful at training myself to add the 3 on the end, and it annoys me to have that overhead (just to remember to add the 3, not typing the one extra character).",{},,User,False
