Ideas on what to try include trying to catch an [Elasticsearch  TransportError](http://elasticsearch-py.readthedocs.io/en/master/exceptions.html#elasticsearch.TransportError) and then test to see if the snapshot exists any more.  It seems like it gives the 404, even if the underlying delete is incomplete.",{},,User,False
