13112,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-04 23:21:59+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,5723682,tjprescott,6844498,Azure,219341019,291669263,"@jtuliani I've taken a look at this. The CLI expands these entries to their fully qualified form when it parses the zone file. Then, to create the record sets, it strips the trailing dot. This is why his entry resolves to ""test.mydomain.com.mydomain.com"". If I try to create the record set with the trailing dot, I get a service error.

I could strip the origin back off (making them relative again), which would fix the user's original issue, but then how would you handle something like:

```
@     600     IN      SOA     ignored.com. hostmaster.mydomain.com. (
                                2017040400
                                28800
                                7200
                                604800
                                600
                                )

test    3600    IN      A       2.2.2.2
$ORIGIN somethingelse.com
other
```
Now other would not resolve to other.somethingelse.com.  Thoughts?
",{},,User,False
