14337,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-24 18:43:18+00:00,5362370,pytest-dev/pytest-rerunfailures,1796208,birdsarah,8897583,pytest-dev,135745179,188400369,"Hi @florianpilz - indeed!

Yes, you've got it - rerun takes precedence so:
* please rerun this flaky test N times
* if it fails after N times, and `-x` is given, then please bail the whole test run.

Having looked into it, I'm confident this is what happens:

