14739,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-16 08:38:43+00:00,66641037,LonamiWebs/Telethon,6297805,Lonami,9887454,LonamiWebs,265524004,336818910,"Nope, it's not possible, a developer of [Unigram](https://github.com/UnigramDev/Unigram) has just confirmed that. Try to add them and get the error. For whatever else you need just [use search](https://lonamiwebs.github.io/Telethon/) or even <kbd>Ctrl+F</kbd> it [here](https://github.com/LonamiWebs/Telethon/blob/master/telethon_generator/scheme.tl)",{},OWNER,User,False
14741,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-07 10:17:14+00:00,66641037,LonamiWebs/Telethon,6297805,Lonami,9887454,LonamiWebs,263631511,334924977,"1. Consider upgrading.
2. This method returns `True` if the user is signed in and can invoke methods like `GetStateRequest` without raising an error. So if it returns `False`, you should `.sign_in`. I have no idea how ""it can return True a few minutes later"". There's probably something weird in your code (and there's not much I can do with this information anyway).",{},OWNER,User,False
14742,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-10 10:32:27+00:00,66641037,LonamiWebs/Telethon,9433226,h-sameri,9887454,LonamiWebs,249293824,321514741,"> Am I using these methods wrongly? Can you provide a minimal working example of getDialogs using an offset?

i dont think so but the only parameter that works is offset_date.
this issue is already mentioned in wiki: https://github.com/LonamiWebs/Telethon/wiki/Retrieving-all-dialogs

``` python
from telethon.tl.functions.messages import GetDialogsRequest
from telethon.tl.types import InputPeerEmpty

dialogs = []
users = []
chats = []

last_date = None
chunk_size = 20
while True:
    result = client(GetDialogsRequest(
                 offset_date=last_date,
                 offset_id=0,
                 offset_peer=InputPeerEmpty(),
                 limit=chunk_size
             ))
    dialogs.extend(result.dialogs)
    users.extend(result.users)
    chats.extend(result.chats)
    last_date = min(msg.date for msg in result.messages)
    if not result.dialogs:
        break
```
 ",{},,User,False
14744,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-11 21:15:20+00:00,66641037,LonamiWebs/Telethon,6297805,Lonami,9887454,LonamiWebs,235089486,307657341,"`_` (underscore) is often used to ignore a value, for instance:
```python
_, entities = client.get_dialogs()
```

It would be better if you changed it for, say, `x`.

Besides this, it looks fine although I cannot test it. I agree it would make it easier to serialize everything as JSON (probably what you need), although accessing the `.__dict__` perhaps would have been enough.",{},,User,False
