14851,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-02 14:11:48+00:00,42750248,watson-developer-cloud/python-sdk,1957636,glennrfisher,10017763,watson-developer-cloud,232950698,305799969,"Unfortunately, I'm busy and won't have a chance to review your changes until next week.

For what it's worth, [here][1] is a commit where I replaced the generated `tone` function with the handwritten `tone` function to avoid breaking changes.

It would be good to add support for multiple content-types, but it might be tricky to do so without a breaking change. For example, on a quick skim of your code, I noticed that the `content_type` parameter is inserted in the middle of the parameter list. That would be a breaking change, because it would break anyone's existing code that is relying on the parameter order rather than the parameter names.

So before merging any changes, we should make sure that they could not break any existing code. That means it must have the same parameter order, and must send the exact same request when `content-type` is left unspecified.

[1]: https://github.com/watson-developer-cloud/python-sdk/pull/198/commits/ac6cfe71d26a26a8c23ed4d7aa57a8d9e71ff461",{},,User,False
