14867,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-28 10:33:03+00:00,84496560,biocommons/hgvs,12969303,ianfab,10083184,biocommons,255149754,332796646,"@reece 
I had a look at the issue with the p.? variant, and found that there are a lot of stop codons in the translated reference sequence when checking it at https://github.com/biocommons/hgvs/blob/234f92e8b0933671b2e129703576c3204ad29748/hgvs/variantmapper.py#L336 during debugging. I then found that there is a programmed ribosomal frameshift in the translation of this transcript (see https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/669250888). So I guess that this could be the reason for the issue, and if so it is perhaps hard to fix this.",{},NONE,User,False
