15016,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-14 19:47:43+00:00,40094312,pyserial/pyserial,1044137,rob-smallshire,10537924,pyserial,159918534,225995052,"In principle, yes, I'd think it's good to transfer ownership to your 'pyserial' organisation. In practice, that looks quite awkward though. I think it's easiest if you:

1. Clone my `pyserial-asyncio` repository locally:

    git clone https://github.com/rob-smallshire/pyserial-asyncio.git

2. Create a new, *completely empty* `pyserial/pyserial-asyncio` GitHub repository owned by your organisation.

3. Update the remote URL for your local clone:

    git remote set-url origin https://github.com/pyserial/pyserial-asyncio.git

4. Push everything to your new GitHub repo:

    git push origin master

Let me know when you're done, and I'll delete my GitHub repo to avoid confusion.
",{},,User,False
