15427,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-17 17:35:12+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,10155819,wintersteiger,11668813,Z3Prover,122768251,165523280,"As far as I can tell there is no file called ""add_01_1_1_reduced.smt2"" in SMTLIB, neither in the latest nor in the previous release. There is a file called ""add_01_1_1.smt2"" which has similar but different content. 

The file content pasted above is not legal SMT2 because of two reasons: 
 - `( FloatingPoint...` should be `(_ FloatingPoint...`
 - some occurrences of symbols are prefixed by `_` and some of them aren't, e.g., `_t_10` vs `t_10`

After fixes those two, the file parses fine for me. ",{},,User,False
