15585,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-20 02:40:40+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,836375,rgbkrk,12401040,nteract,324676096,390453430,"Awesome! Thanks for taking the jupyter extension for a spin!

This whole setup can be synchronous and part of the connected menu I think.

* `window.open` is synchronous (and there's not an asynchronous variant)
* `window.open`'s side effect doesn't change anything on our page

You are right in catching if `window.open` failed or not since it can return `null`. 🤔 I suppose we need a flow for popup handling detection.

However! There's another way to do this without having to deal with any JS issues. Create an `<a>` link that matches the style in the menu, likely like this:

```
<a href=""/nteract/edit"" target=""_blank"">Open Directory View</a>
```

Since this comes from user interaction, it doesn't count towards the browser's built in pop up throttling.

As an aside, the nteract logo in the upper left also has the behavior of navigating up a directory and showing the directory listing (though it's clearly a kinda hidden feature).",{},MEMBER,User,False
