15743,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-23 21:54:45+00:00,36355765,angr/archinfo,2411,mattrepl,12520807,angr,209646946,282133754,"@rhelmot I'm preparing a fix for PPC32 to include the argument position info. I'll try a new software engineering best practice I've heard about called ""test your f'n code"" before sending the pull request.

That said, do you know which header/script was used to update the registers in those files? The PPC32 register offsets don't match with the libvex header files included with pyvex. I'm hesitant to update them all without knowing what was intended.",{},,User,False
