15938,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-04 16:31:40+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,138223754,192344678,"These tests are now much closer to passing but I'm seeing that the job XML is not being updated after the job is submitted.
After the meeting yesterday I thought we agreed that at the very least the job should trigger a flush after being submitted but preferably it should trigger a flush before submitting and after splitting so that the result of the splitting (potentially a _very_ expensive operation) is saved.",{},,User,False
15942,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-30 15:46:39+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,13677368,drmarkwslater,13271048,ganga-devs,172943374,263907600,"The problem I have with this code at the moment is the duel inheritance of `GangaException` and `KeyError`. It really should be one or the other because otherwise you could `catch` things you weren't expecting. Ideally, I feel it **should** be shifted to `GangaKeyError` but it seems there are currently so many places where `KeyError` is caught instead that I couldn't get this to work after quite a bit of trying. 

I suppose for the moment I'll revert back to the `GangaKeyError` but with a note that this should be fixed in the future. ",{},,User,False
15945,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-10 08:18:41+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,61316,milliams,13271048,ganga-devs,153790699,218089446,I will add a test or two which check this explicitly.,{},,User,False
15948,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-07 10:02:08+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,138522205,193187733,"Why isn't the Job in this case calling ```_flush``` I'm not exactly won over by passing the equivalent of 'flush now' to a queue which may be busy with things like parallel submit and so will _not_ process this for much, much longer than 30sec.
Either way if this is a 6.1.18 development I'm keen to restore the expected behavior we talked about in the meeting in 6.1.17 to have some level of opportunistic flushing on job status changes.

I'm much, _much_ more in favor of making the user wait (at most 30sec-1min on AFS) to flush a very large job and have some level of safety in the job vs relying on a 'try and flush around now' system. It's a big change to what we've previously discussed and I'd be happier letting 6.1.17 get out with some level of belt and braces on the safety of the users data.
Yes this is heavy-handed but I'd rather be heavy-handed as then I can sleep at night rather than worrying about the next time users manage to configure things such that they lose data.",{},,User,False
