There is now a difference in behaviour of different parts of the code based upon the state of the configuration in the test. This is obviously not ideal and so I'm going to have a go at correcting the tests to make sure that the correct code paths are being tested and not just ones which happen to be safe.",{},,User,False
15953,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-27 13:04:32+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,128868803,175610049,"OK, I'm more than happy to have ```__repr__``` do something a bit more sane :). I'm assuming people using ```import ganga``` are likely experienced users who don't need the 'hand-holding' provided by ```__repr_pretty__```.

I'm a little concerned that none of the above behind the proxy are suitable for replacing a lot of the logic in ```export(myJob)```.
I think modifying the ```__repr__``` to show non-copyable objects behind the proxy is more correct as the proxy is the thing which stops us from changing/copying/setting objects. If we want the exact representation of the object we want to know what this is set to.
You could argue this would allow ```import(myJobFile.txt)``` to subvert the proxy but it already should if it's working correctly imo.

I would propose:

GangaObject         | `__repr__` | `_repr_pretty_` | `__str__` 
------------------|------------|-----------------|----------------
Show transient | ✗ | ✗ | ✗

Proxy         | `__repr__` | `_repr_pretty_` | `__str__` 
------------------|------------|-----------------|----------------
Show transient | ✗ | ✓ | ✓

