15997,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-04 15:50:37+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,131693407,192330206,"The GangaList changes are hiding the fact that the interfaces in the Tasks system (Core and LHCb) are passing around proxied and un-proxied object inconsistently atm. This reduces the problem as the GangaList has it's own layers of stripProxy before storing elements.
Yes It would be ideal to track this down and clean every interface but frankly we should add a proxy decorator which classes can import and then it becomes a much quicker task to fix what's going on.

A good 75% of the code is needed to get the LHCb tasks working as expected but I was seeing deadlocks in testing I was unable to get past.
Hopefully this has improved based upon latest changed but I still need to get the XML tests fixed then I'll come back to this.

This branch also adds a minor change to the Schema to allow the use of GangaList in the Schema. The only real changes dropped in a minimal implementation are some switches to GangaList in the tasks section, the code 'cleanup' in the Repo and a few large sections of commented out code being removed.

My proposal is that I'd like to merge this if the deadlocks in #271 have gone away in recent develop I'd like to push for merge. If #271 is still a problem then this code (which largely deals with bugs only experienced by Tasks) is not worth putting in as users won't be able to use it.

eta about another hour or so before I can say if #271 is an issue",{},,User,False
