16198,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-11 15:14:29+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,871903,ddiakopoulos,14095512,IntelRealSense,140143744,195407922,@vidstige We have no control over the serial numbers that the firmware (or usb descriptor) hands back so we'll just need to work through this in software. I'm inclined to trim the trailing space on SR300 numbers. We can already distinguish between F200 and SR300 based on VID/PID. ,{},,User,False
16199,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-03 16:55:03+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,6958867,dorodnic,14095512,IntelRealSense,207390334,291204130,"@nwestbury, perhaps I didn't understand the issue correctly. Different models of SR300 are reporting `port_id` differently because some manufacturers choose to include internal USB hub inside the camera case, and some don't. The goal of `get_port_id` is to distinguish between devices based on physical location and not concrete serial numbers. On-board USB-hubs certainly complicate things a bit, but we can't know from code if the USB-hub is part of the device or not (hope this makes sense). 
Could you please clarify your question, perhaps add the output from `lsusb -t` for both devices?",{},,User,False
