16350,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-04 17:33:42+00:00,43056951,graphql-python/graphene,188257,syrusakbary,15002022,graphql-python,127047499,179958910,"@dwiel if you wrap your fields with common attributes to a `ObjectType`, as @Globegitter suggested, the resolver for this `ObjectType` will be only called once.

So yes, resolving field would be called 3 times.

1. The parent resolver (`helloPing`)
2. The hello field in `HelloPing`
3. The ping field in `HelloPing`

However, as `GraphQL` (and `graphene` as well) is prepared to run the resolving fields asynchronously, this is how the nature of resolving queries should look like (as defined by the Spec, when querying we cannot assure that the fields would resolved in order, hence we cannot depend on other fields resolve value in the same type level).",{},,User,False
