16509,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-04 15:35:14+00:00,91379993,tensorflow/tensorboard,4317806,wchargin,15658638,tensorflow,246424475,320280359,"@rryan: Fantastic—thank you for the detailed input.

> Ability to include [string tensor] text annotations would be amazing.

So far 2/2 people expressing support for this…noted!

We have some flexibility here, as we haven’t designed the audio tensor format yet. The current summary includes a bunch of global metadata: the sample rate, channel count, number of samples, and MIME type. All of this is junk: the only field among these that’s even used is the content type, but that is always `audio/wav`.[1] So, if we remove all these, then the tensor would look like a rank-1 string tensor of `[wav_data_0, wav_data_1, …]`. Perhaps we could instead use a rank-2 string tensor of the form `[[wav_data_0, wav_data_1, …], [markdown_metadata_0, markdown_metadata_1, …]]`, which would allow you to provide a transcript or any other information that you like. This could easily come from a string tensor.

[1]: TensorFlow only supports encoding WAV, sadly. If this changes in the future and we really want to add support for storing the content type in the summary, we could include this in the summary metadata instead of the summary value.

> spectrogram plot tool

An interesting idea: I can see how this would be indispensable. We’d have to design this carefully with performance in mind (where do we do the FFTs?). I’m going to punt on this for now, as it would be a major undertaking…

I don’t know what you mean by, ""I'd ideally like my model to be able to write a webcomponent to the events file that TB would embed."" Surely you don’t mean that you want your TensorFlow code to be emitting JavaScript and HTML source code to be injected into the TensorBoard dashboard?

> Audio summaries reload every 30 seconds by default, which is quite annoying!

I imagine that we can be more careful about not reloading the UI when the backing data doesn't change. I’ll take a look. (I’m assuming that you do want it to fetch new data, but you don’t want it to reset your playback position/checkpoint every 30s?)

> Download button (please keep it, but ideally the filename could be better than ""individualAudio"" with no extensions)

We don’t plan to remove this. Note that it’s provided by the native controls of the HTML `<audio>` element; after searching a bit, I don’t see a way to change the downloaded file name. However, I’m happy to add a link above (by the step counter, maybe) to download it, and with a user-created link it is easy to set the download name. This could replace the download button in the controls. Would you be interested in this?

> It probably makes sense to turn off repeat by default. I like it, but it can be annoying e.g. when you left one playing and change pages (it still plays on repeat).

I can easily change this, and I can also easily make it a dashboard-level global option. (I.e., a single checkbox “loop audio?” would appear above the runs selector.)

> Scrub through checkpoints -- this feature is awesome, please keep it!

Certainly.

> nice way of grouping identical tag audio across runs

Just to be sure—it should still be the case that all occurrences of a given tag are consecutive, right? The only change is that they might wrap across lines. (If this isn’t the case, I’ll fix it.) I’m surprised that this is very much worse than having them all in one row, so I just want to confirm.

One thing that you can do is search for the tag, which will remove all other tags (if you anchor it with `^tag_name$`). I appreciate that this is not as convenient.

> Let me know if you'd like to see our typical tensorboards (or just check out my experiments internally).

I downloaded one while looking into a YAQS question of yours, and my biggest impression was how huge the files were. How much trouble is caused by the fact that we only support WAV and not, say, Vorbis? Currently, TensorFlow only supports encoding WAV, but I don’t see why this should need to be the case. [Adding arguments `{""-f"", StrCat(output_format_id)}` to `ffmpeg_lib.cc`](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/359d6f9716c0bb9bd8201ce600da98b0481a8049/tensorflow/contrib/ffmpeg/default/ffmpeg_lib.cc#L41) should do it. Is this something that you would like to see?
",{},,User,False
