16627,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-25 20:08:16+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,290693569,360585197,"@VictorAtPL, I did a quick review of your code and did not notice anything obvious.  I also tested your code with posix platform and it seemed to work fine.  I suspect that this is an issue specific to the CC2538 platform.

The Joiner Finalize message is used to trigger application and/or vendor-specific provisioning.  See Thread 1.1.1 Section 8.4.5 for more details.

The ""hangs"" you see during mbedtls crypto operations are expected.  The CC2538 example drivers do not implement platform-specific acceleration of elliptic curve crypto operations.

In your ""update"", you indicated that the same issue occurs with a CLI-based joiner built clean from GitHub master branch?",{},OWNER,User,False
