16931,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-17 16:40:23+00:00,1553944,wireservice/csvkit,98301,danvk,17111824,wireservice,66959570,254262195,"Copying over this comment from #525...

In case it helps anyone else, you can lowercase all column names in a Postgres database after you import using [this magical incantation][1] from Stack Overflow:

```sql
\t on
select 'ALTER TABLE '||'""'||table_name||'""'||' RENAME COLUMN '||'""'||column_name||'""'||' TO ' || lower(column_name)||';' 
from information_schema.columns 
where table_schema = 'public' and lower(column_name) != column_name
\g /tmp/go_to_lower
\i /tmp/go_to_lower
```

[1]: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10086532/how-can-i-convert-all-columns-in-my-database-to-case-insensitive/10088351#10088351",{},,User,False
