17025,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-05 13:00:45+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,1203629,wjakob,17565521,pybind,205312954,277518302,"I think this is great and will solve a number of recurring difficulties with method resolution. It's nice that all of this also integrates with the existing implicit conversions for custom types and extends them to builtin types. My vote would be to merge this one and close the other PR.

I find the ``ExampleMandA`` change a bit troubling -- to me, this seems to indicate that an ``ExampleMandA`` instance is leaked somwhere else. But this does not make much sense: it only occurs in two testcases, and both of them test that the reference count is zero at the end. I think it would be good to track down what is causing this rather than committing a workaround.",{},,User,False
