17339,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-27 23:54:31+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,260937517,332687977,"@drandreaskrueger thanks for testing.

> - separate (submitting that transaction & querying transaction receipt) into 2 API calls?
>   - 1st API call: Submit transaction, answer is transaction hash
>   - 2nd API call: with transaction hash given, return status

This was intentionally avoided. Using two calls won't really help since the problem with timeouts will just move from the 1st API call to the 2nd.

> what else could be done?

We can block the HTTP response until the transaction is mined, this has it's on set of problems, since a long running http request may seem broken to a user.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
