17376,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-09 12:53:08+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,248364738,411746805,"I think we should first start with our preferred data format, and then look at libraries. There are tons of formats available:

- [avro](https://avro.apache.org/)
- [thrift](https://thrift.apache.org/)
- [msgpack](https://msgpack.org/)
- [flatbuffers](https://github.com/google/flatbuffers)
- [json](https://json.org/)
- [rlp](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/RLP)
- [pickle](https://docs.python.org/3/library/pickle.html)

(and a few more I cant remember now)

We need to decide if the data format:

- Should it be indexable by a database or are we writing indexes by hand?
- Should it be versioned/upgradable or are we doing it by hand? 
- Should it be binary or human readable?
- Should it be used exclusively for the WAL or also for node communication?

Then for libraries:

- Should it have native support for python or external compilers are fine?
- Should it have a support for different languages or just python is good enough?
- What about performance for encoding/decoding and memory usage?",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
