17458,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-17 01:03:22+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,917985,gaow,20074389,vatlab,248227082,322940244,"I understand what it does. But I'm talking about removing ""obsolete"" signatures of a project. For example, the code for the project has been changed many times and generated a lot of signatures / task err/out files that will never ever be of any value. Then when a person finally is settled with the project, he can use someting like `sos purge --obsolete` to remove any signatures historically related to the project, but will not touch any of the most up-to-date signatures so that executing SoS again will not trigger reruns for the same project.",{},,User,False
