17609,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-22 13:54:28+00:00,76210069,pytorch/text,1612863,chrishokamp,21003710,pytorch,352954154,415039909,"Hi I guess it's [this line](https://github.com/pytorch/text/blob/7ab2ee56c3590ec112da81cf09dcc057c0563b6b/torchtext/data/dataset.py#L248) that's taking a long time. But after `self.examples` has been created, you should be able to pickle it. So a hackish way would be to load your dataset once, then pickle `self.examples`, then afterwards create a dummy `TabularDataset` with the same fields but a tiny dataset, unpickle your examples, then set `dataset.examples = unpickled_examples`.  A better way would be to change the logic so that iterators are used everywhere, and re-created once they're extinguished. ",{},NONE,User,False
