17661,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-01 22:28:11+00:00,72477752,pulumi/pulumi,1871912,swgillespie,21992475,pulumi,346426763,409745596,"Luke's right, this is going to show `replacing...` for all replaced resources until the very end of the plan, when we start to retire deletes. Though it's unfortunate from a UX perspective, it's unfortunately true... we truly don't complete a replacement until the old resource is deleted.

I thought about this for a while today and I think I'm OK with this. The thing in my mind that is good about this new change is that, now, something is happening in the UI when we are retiring deletes - we're changing rows from ""replacing..."" to ""replaced"". Today it looks like the CLI is completely idle while we do deletes in the background. I do appreciate in this case that users will be able to see deletes as they happen, even if it's not obvious *what* they are seeing.",{},MEMBER,User,False
