17706,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-19 23:30:59+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,249517,robertnishihara,22125274,ray-project,342857851,406444624,"Just to clarify, ""Redis"" and the ""plasma store"" are two separate things.

We use the plasma store to store data (e.g., objects returned by tasks).

We use Redis to store metadata, e.g., specifications of tasks (which are used to rerun tasks if necessary) and data about which objects live on which machines (we actually start multiple Redis servers).",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
