17782,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-21 03:32:25+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,19584326,guoyuhong,22125274,ray-project,352181051,414538691,"@pcmoritz  Hi Philipp, thanks for the comments. We introduce `log4cplus` because of the following 2 reasons:
1. The most important reason is that `log4cplus` supports user-defined log format. In this PR, I provide a default format of `%d{%m/%d/%y %H:%M:%S}  - %m [%l]%n` which can be changed. However, if we use only `glog`, we need to add some derived class to change the format.
2. From the perf test, `log4cplus` is better than `glog`.

I accept that supporting both libs increases the maintenance overhead. However, at the same time, it provides us with flexibility.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
