17843,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-27 12:49:46+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,16033421,beardypig,22243823,streamlink,238308624,318352140,"I imagine there was some sports game being broadcast on one of the channels, and someone got the HLS URL and posted it to some forum... or something similar.",{},,User,False
17846,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-26 16:32:01+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,16033421,beardypig,22243823,streamlink,197520919,269225012,"There isn't a correct/good way to do this, `RTMPStream` uses the `pbs` package to run `rtmpdump` and I don't think that it supports multiple arguments with the same name. `pbs` is also not maintained anymore, `sh` is suggested as an alternative so maybe we can migrate to that and improve the API for `RTMPStream`. 

It looks like all of the vendored packages might need reviewing/updating, I'd personally like to remove a couple of them and just add them as regular dependencies (unless they have streamlink only patches, but it's better to avoid those or subclass, as you suggested in the other issue for flashmedia). ",{},,User,False
17849,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-15 21:28:26+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,16033421,beardypig,22243823,streamlink,323381412,389319380,"Looks like there is another bug going on there too. But, with regards to cable logins; we have discussed it before and we decided before that it would not be feasible to support. As far as I know each cable provider has their own login page, and it uses some kind of federated login. Which means we’d have to implement a lot of different pages. I’d be willing to investigate it again, but I don’t have (and I don’t think any other Streamlink member has) a cable login to investigate with :)

For us to develop and maintain support for those cable logins, we’d need an account for each of them. But like I said, it’s not from lack of want but from lack of resources :)",{},MEMBER,User,False
