18294,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-11 00:09:31+00:00,102692863,onnx/onnx,4958441,jerryzh168,31675368,onnx,264394003,335643481,"Please refer to http://deeplearning.net/software/theano/tutorial/conv_arithmetic.html#transposed-convolution-arithmetic, 

A transposed convolution specified by
input size i,
kernel size k,
stride s,
padding size p,
has an output size given by
o = s (i - 1) + a + k - 2p, a in {0, ..., s - 1}
where a is a user-specified quantity used to distinguish between the s different possible output sizes.
",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
